title: Theo Walcott Says Some of Arsenal's Young Players Don't Know Who Thierry Henry Is
text:
Arsenal's young guns just lost a whole lot of credibility.
Gunners hitman Theo Walcott has sensationally claimed that some of the club's crop of young players don't know the name of the club's all-time greatest legend, Thierry Henry .
Henry became Arsenal's all-time record goalscorer during an incredible spell in London that also saw him land two Premier League titles between 1999 and 2007. He returned to the club as an academy coach earlier this year but according to Arsenal's current number 14, it's not as exciting for some of the prospects as it perhaps should be.
Speaking to the Evening Standard , Walcott said:
"Some are only 13 or 14 and they’re playing under-18s because they’re that good – so some didn’t know who he was...t hey know who he is now."
It sounds like Arsenal's academy need to hit YouTube.
We're not sure anyone with an interest in football and over the age of 10 can not know Thierry Henry. Should we really believe, you Theo?
[via Evening Standard ]
